For a simple relative comparison of materials, we direct a laser beam with 1/$e^2$ diameter $\approx$\,1\,mm to intersect the axis of rotation of a turntable, with the sample of interest at its center.  The sample and detector photodiode may be rotated independently about this axis.  A chopper wheel modulates the incident light power $P_{\rm{i}}$ at 3\,kHz, and the reflected power $P_{\rm{r}}$ is extracted from the detector photodiode signal using a lock-in amplifier.
